records.addlTxt: Converted to a signature bond.

State asks court to amend cash bond to a signature bond with just the standard conditions. Defense has no objection. Court amends cash bond to $1,000 signature bond. Standard conditions as stated on the bond apply.
Deferred Acceptance of Guilty Plea Agreement

Minute sheet. State amends Ct. 1 to 5 separate counts of Unlawful Use of Computer Communications pursuant to 947.0125(2)(c). Ct. 2 from original complaint now becomes Ct. 6. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Cts. 1 - 6.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Cts. 1 - 5. Court withholds accepting of the plea on Ct. 6 to allow defendant time to complete terms of Deferred Acceptance of Guilty Plea Agreement. Court reviews collateral consequence, possible penalties if defendant would be found guilty of a felony.  Upon successful completion of DAGPA, State will, after 4 years, move to dismiss Ct. 6.  Court reviews DAGPA with defendant, approves and signs agreement. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation regarding Cts. 1 - 5. Defendant apologizes to the court. Bond remains in effect regarding Ct. 6.

Defendant Jose B Garcia Jauregui in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file.  Defense waives reading of Information, indicates defendant would is accepting the State's offer and would like to conclude matter today.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for December 23, 2019 at 11:45 am.

Defendant Jose B Garcia Jauregui in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file.    Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.  Arraignment scheduled for January 6, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Jose B Garcia Jauregui in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Raymond L. Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel, right to prelim. Defense waives reading of the complaint, waives time limit for prelim. Atty Pelrine requests a status be set vs setting matter for prelim. Defense has no objection. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for October 27, 2014 at 10:30 am.
